title Changing Consumer Behaviour and Transport Demand (May 2022)
style wardley

// Anchors — three user types
anchor Government [0.98, 0.55]
anchor Transport Public [0.98, 0.70]
anchor Transport Operators [0.97, 0.60]

// Layer 1 — user journey (A-to-B needs)
component Ease of Use [0.90, 0.55]
component Cost [0.89, 0.75]
component Access to Service [0.88, 0.65]
component Personal Safety [0.87, 0.55]
component Physical Safety [0.86, 0.70]
component Awareness [0.85, 0.50]

// Layer 2 — transport information stack
component Transport Integration [0.75, 0.40]
component Situational Services [0.72, 0.35]
component Mobility Hubs [0.70, 0.30]

// Layer 3 — mode choice
component Private Mode [0.62, 0.75]
component Shared Mode [0.60, 0.45]
component Distributed Public Mode [0.58, 0.35]

// Virtual alternative — displaces demand
component Virtual Space (Zoom) [0.68, 0.80]

// Shocks that reshape demand (external driver)
component Demand Shocks (Pandemic, Fuel) [0.78, 0.20]

// Layer 4 — vehicles
component Car [0.48, 0.80]
component Train [0.46, 0.65]

// Layer 5 — connectivity and cybersecurity
component Connectivity [0.38, 0.82]
component Cybersecurity [0.36, 0.55]

// Layer 6 — planning and regulation
component City Planning [0.42, 0.35]
component Regulation [0.40, 0.30]
component Sustainability and Climate Policy [0.44, 0.30]

// Layer 7 — infrastructure (public vs private) and CNI
component Public Infrastructure [0.25, 0.55]
component Private Infrastructure [0.24, 0.70]
component Critical National Infrastructure [0.12, 0.60]

// Dependencies (A->B means A depends on B)

// Anchors to journey needs
Transport Public->Ease of Use
Transport Public->Cost
Transport Public->Access to Service
Transport Public->Personal Safety
Transport Public->Physical Safety
Transport Public->Awareness
Government->Access to Service
Government->Physical Safety
Government->Sustainability and Climate Policy
Government->Regulation
Transport Operators->Cost
Transport Operators->Access to Service
Transport Operators->Awareness

// Journey needs → information stack
Ease of Use->Transport Integration
Access to Service->Transport Integration
Access to Service->Mobility Hubs
Awareness->Situational Services
Cost->Transport Integration

// Journey needs → mode choice (direct relationship)
Ease of Use->Shared Mode
Ease of Use->Distributed Public Mode
Cost->Private Mode
Cost->Shared Mode
Personal Safety->Private Mode
Personal Safety->Distributed Public Mode

// Journey needs → virtual alternative (displacement)
Ease of Use->Virtual Space (Zoom)
Cost->Virtual Space (Zoom)

// Information stack → mode choice
Transport Integration->Shared Mode
Transport Integration->Distributed Public Mode
Transport Integration->Private Mode
Situational Services->Distributed Public Mode
Situational Services->Shared Mode
Mobility Hubs->Shared Mode
Mobility Hubs->Distributed Public Mode

// Shocks reshape demand — sit above mode choice as forcing input
Demand Shocks (Pandemic, Fuel)->Private Mode
Demand Shocks (Pandemic, Fuel)->Distributed Public Mode
Demand Shocks (Pandemic, Fuel)->Virtual Space (Zoom)

// Mode choice → vehicles
Private Mode->Car
Distributed Public Mode->Train
Distributed Public Mode->Car
Shared Mode->Car

// Information stack / virtual → connectivity and cyber
Transport Integration->Connectivity
Situational Services->Connectivity
Virtual Space (Zoom)->Connectivity
Connectivity->Cybersecurity

// Vehicles → connectivity (modern telematics)
Car->Connectivity
Train->Connectivity

// Planning, regulation, sustainability
Transport Integration->City Planning
Mobility Hubs->City Planning
City Planning->Regulation
City Planning->Sustainability and Climate Policy
Private Mode->Regulation
Shared Mode->Regulation
Distributed Public Mode->Regulation
Car->Regulation
Train->Regulation
Sustainability and Climate Policy->Regulation

// Infrastructure layer
Car->Public Infrastructure
Car->Private Infrastructure
Train->Public Infrastructure
Train->Private Infrastructure
Connectivity->Private Infrastructure
City Planning->Public Infrastructure
Mobility Hubs->Public Infrastructure
Public Infrastructure->Critical National Infrastructure
Private Infrastructure->Critical National Infrastructure
Connectivity->Critical National Infrastructure
Cybersecurity->Critical National Infrastructure

// Inertia markers — the "lagging" components flagged by the scenario
component Regulation [0.40, 0.30] inertia
component Public Infrastructure [0.25, 0.55] inertia
component City Planning [0.42, 0.35] inertia

// Evolution movements (scenario, not forecast — consumer behaviour driving the wave)
evolve Shared Mode 0.65
evolve Distributed Public Mode 0.55
evolve Transport Integration 0.60
evolve Situational Services 0.55
evolve Mobility Hubs 0.45
evolve Virtual Space (Zoom) 0.90

// Strategic notes
note Consumer-behaviour driven evolution [0.78, 0.50]
note Infrastructure / regulation lag zone [0.30, 0.25]
note Displacement pressure from virtual [0.70, 0.85]
